Sentencas: BaCe0.8Sm0.1Gd0.1O3-delta, material for an electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells, was prepared by a newly sol-combustion method to obtain fine grain size and good sinterability
Titulo: Synthesis of BaCe0.8Sm0.1Gd0.1O3-δ electrolyte by a sol-combustion method

Sentencas: The phase formation, sinterability and electrical conductivity were focused on by this study.
Titulo: Synthesis of BaCe0.8Sm0.1Gd0.1O3-δ electrolyte by a sol-combustion method

Sentencas: The results show that nano-sized BaCe0.8Sm0.1Gd0.1O3-delta powders with single orthorhombic perovskite structure were prepared by this process successfully.
Titulo: Synthesis of BaCe0.8Sm0.1Gd0.1O3-δ electrolyte by a sol-combustion method

Sentencas: The powders showed high sinterability, and a relative of 95.2% of the theoretical density was obtained at a sintering temperature of 1400 degrees C. Electrochemistry measurements showed that the BaCe0.8Sm0.1Gd0.1O3-delta ceramics had relatively high oxygen ionic conductivity in low-temperature range.
Titulo: Synthesis of BaCe0.8Sm0.1Gd0.1O3-δ electrolyte by a sol-combustion method
